ce:section.ce:para:
In recent years, many fluorescence sensors have been developed for the detection of bacteria, among which FRET-based fluorescent sensors are particularly popular due to their simple structural design and high sensitivity. With the development of material technology, more and more materials are being used as donors and acceptors. Therefore, in this section, we will introduce some commonly used materials and their applications under different strategies to support the above description of the construction strategies (Table 1
                     ). This section is divided into three categories for introduction: relatively conventional organic fluorescent dyes, nanomaterials with excellent properties, and quenchers that often appear as acceptors (Table 2
                     ). Structures, synthetic methods of some materials, methods of modification, and optical properties are presented. Then we focus on the applications of the material as the donor or acceptor based on different construction strategies.
